summary: This is an email chain between US Attorney's Office personnel discussing a deposition where an unnamed individual invoked their Fifth Amendment right against self-incrimination. The emails reference attaching related legal filings.

persons.name: Unknown Female Deponent
persons.context: An unnamed individual who gave a deposition in litigation and invoked her Fifth Amendment right for every question.

events.title: Deposition with Fifth Amendment Invocation
events.description: An unnamed female deponent gave a deposition in litigation and invoked her Fifth Amendment right against self-incrimination for every question asked.

keyFacts: An unnamed female individual gave a deposition in litigation related to the Epstein case.
The deponent invoked her Fifth Amendment right against self-incrimination for every question asked.
The email exchange shows US Attorney's Office personnel discussing and sharing related legal filings on December 23, 2019.
The document references multiple PDF attachments with numerical identifiers (e.g., 127126085966.pdf).
The email suggests the deponent's lawyer made a 'good call' by advising her to invoke the Fifth Amendment.
